{"title": "Kari the Elephant (Version 2)", "description": "Kari the Elephant is a 1922 work by Dhan Gopal Mukerji. The book is the first among those written in English by an Indian author in the category of children's literature. Kari the Elephant is a bildungsroman narrative that unravels the relationship shared by the protagonist boy and Kari the elephant and the adventures the boy, along with Kari and Kope, the pet monkey go through living by the edge of the forest is quite mesmerizing. Their relationship grows stronger with each adventure and their lives defy the boundaries between human and animal society. Set in a colonial Indian village, the treatment of nature and natural life along with the infiltration of capitalist mindset runs as a background to this narrative that eventually endangers this unique relationship the boy and Kari share. (Summary by Mahimaraj)", "duration": 9644, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "10315", "name": "Dhan Gopal Mukerji"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/karitheelephant_2112_librivox/karitheelephant_2112.jpg", "copyright_year": "1922", "genres": ["Action & Adventure", "Animals & Nature"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Mahimaraj"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Mahimaraj"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Oreki"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Bringing Up Kari", "readers": [16699], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/karitheelephant_2112_librivox/karitheelephant_01_mukerji_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1151}, {"section": 2, "title": "How Kari Saved Our Lives", "readers": [16699], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/karitheelephant_2112_librivox/karitheelephant_02_mukerji_64kb.mp3", "duration": 659}, {"section": 3, "title": "Kari Goes to Town", "readers": [16699], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/karitheelephant_2112_librivox/karitheelephant_03_mukerji_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1320}, {"section": 4, "title": "K